<h3 class="date"><a href="/2007/apr/18/">&#x27a0;</a> April 18, 2007</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="format-war-soliders-syncd-hd-d" >

        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://gizmodo.com/gadgets/home-entertainment/format-war-soliders-syncd-hd+dvd-purchase-by-fanboys-spike-amazon-rank-blu+rayers-set-to-retaliate-253131.php">Format War Soliders: Sync&#39;d HD-DVD Purchase by Fanboys Spike Amazon Rank, Blu-Rayers Set To Retaliate - Gizmodo</a></h4>

        
            
        

        <p>A couple of hundred HD-DVD fanboys did an organized reverse-boycott, all purchasing HD-DVD discs on Amazon on the same day to try and prove&#8230; something.  Not quite sure what.  Really it emphasizes how lousy both formats are doing that a sales graph can be moved so dramatically by a few hundred customers.</p>

